# 3. Core Principles

## 3.1 Photonic Confinement

The reactor attempts to maintain high-density photon circulation inside a controlled chamber.

Objectives:

* Increase photon interaction time
* Reduce escape losses
* Increase conversion opportunities
* Improve thermal coupling

---

## 3.2 Hydrogen Interaction

Hydrogen serves as:

* Energy carrier
* Thermal transfer medium
* Spectral interaction medium

Theoretical benefits:

* Improved energy density
* Faster heat distribution
* Enhanced conversion pathways

---

## 3.3 Spectral Conversion

Incoming energy is transformed into wavelengths optimized for conversion systems.

Purpose:

* Reduce unusable radiation
* Increase TPV efficiency
* Improve thermal utilization

---

## 3.4 Multi-Layer Energy Recovery

Traditional systems often lose energy as:

* Heat
* Radiation
* Reflection

PCTM-10000-X seeks to recover energy across multiple layers simultaneously.

